\par }{\b\insrsid2628021\charrsid2628021 CORE COURSE III \endash  TEXTILE SCIENCE
\par }{\b\insrsid2628021\charrsid6900382 
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid3866909 {\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid13528374 OBJECTIVES
\par }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 To enable the students to Under the textile fibers, their properties and uses. Impart knowledge on spinning, fabric production 
\par }{\insrsid13528374 
\par }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid13528374 U}{\b\insrsid13528374 nit }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid13528374 -I\tab }{\b\insrsid13528374 \tab }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid13528374 (15 Hours)
\par }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 Fiber \endash 
 Definition, Meaning, Classification of Textiles Fibers- Natural fiber-cotton, Flax, silk, wool- origin, manufacturing process, properties and end uses. Minor Textile fibers-, properties and uses. Regenerated fibers-Rayon and acetate-origin, manufacturing
 process, properties and end uses.
\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid13528374 U}{\b\insrsid13528374 nit}{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid13528374 -II\tab (20 Hours)
\par }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 {\*\bkmkstart page8}{\*\bkmkend page8}Synthetic fibers-Nylon, Dacron, Orlon and Acrylic- origin, manufacturing process, properties and end uses. Spinning \endash Definition, meaning, types of spinning. Yarn and Twist 
\endash  Definition, counts of yarns. Meaning and Classification natural manmade of yarns and Novelty yarns. Blends and Mixtures (understanding concepts only)
\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid13528374 U}{\b\insrsid13528374 nit}{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid13528374 -III\tab (20 Hours)
\par }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 Weaving- Definition, Meaning, parts and functions of simple loom. Types of weaves- Basic weaves and fan
cy weaves, Non-woven knitting- Definition, Meaning, classification of knitting, Knotting, Lacing, Braiding, Bonding and Felting. (Understanding of the concepts only).
\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid13528374 U}{\b\insrsid13528374 nit }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid13528374 -IV\tab (15 Hours)
\par }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 Wet processing- Importance of Wet processing of textiles- Fiber, Yar
n, and Fabric processing. Basic finishes-Singeing, Desizing, Scouring bleaches, Mercerizing, Napping, Sanforizing, Special finishes, finishes suitable to Natural and manmade fibers.
\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid13528374 U}{\b\insrsid13528374 nit }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid13528374 -V\tab (20 Hours)
\par }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 Dyeing- Definition of Dyes, Meaning and concept of Dyes, Classification of dyes, Dyes suitability to various fibers. Methods of Dyeing- Printing \endash 
 Definition, Methods of printing-Block printing, Roller, Screen, Resist Printing \endash Batik, Tie and Dye, stencil.
\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid13528374 RELATED EXPERIENCES}{\b\insrsid6777019 
\par }{\b\insrsid13528374\charrsid13528374 
\par }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 Fiber, Yarn and Fabric \endash  Identification
\par Simple Hand stitches- preparation of the samples
\par Seams, Types of Seams- preparation of the samples using hand sewing
\par Embroidery \endash  preparation of the samples
\par Fullness- preparation of sample in each types using hand sewing
