\qc \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid16343273 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\insrsid16343273 {\*\bkmkstart page19}{\*\bkmkend page19}I YEAR \endash  II SEMESTER 
\par COURSE CODE \endash  }{\b\insrsid9724074 5}{\b\insrsid16343273 MHF2C3
\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid16343273\charrsid16343273 CORE COURSE VI}{\b\insrsid16343273 I}{\b\insrsid16343273\charrsid16343273  \endash  }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid16343273 FAMILY RESOURCE MANAGEMENT
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid3866909 {\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 
\par }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid16343273 OBJECTIVES
\par }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid16343273 {\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 To enable the students to}{\insrsid16343273  }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 
Understand the factors motivating management Acquire ability to use human resources Gain knowledge about management of family resources Know the importance of decisions in management Understand the functions of market, consumer problems and protection 

\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid3866909 {\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 
\par }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid16343273 U}{\b\insrsid16343273 nit }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid16343273 -I\tab }{\b\insrsid16343273 \tab }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid16343273 (15Hours)
\par }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 
\par Factors motivating management: Human Values- meaning, sources, origin, characteristics, factors influencing values, changes in values and their causes. Goal-types, characteristics, factors influencing goals, Standards-conventional and mod
ern, flexible and rigid. Introduction to Management, concept and definition of management, Management in family living-importance, managerial function of families
\par }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid16343273 
\par U}{\b\insrsid16343273 nit }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid16343273 -II\tab (15 Hours)
\par }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 {\*\bkmkstart page20}{\*\bkmkend page20}
\par Resources and their management in the family-Resources - de
finition, characteristics, usefulness of resources, classification of resources, factors affecting the use of resources, guidelines for the use of resources, Decision making- steps in decision making, types. Management Process-Planning, controlling and ev
aluating.
\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid16343273 U}{\b\insrsid16343273 nit }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid16343273  \endash III}{\b\insrsid16343273\charrsid16343273 \tab }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid16343273 (20 Hours)
\par }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 
\par Management of time and Money -Management of time -Characteristics and nature of time, Tools in time management- time cost, time norms, peak loads, work units, work curves, rest periods. Process of managing time-Planning, Co
ntrolling and evaluating. Management of money-Definition, types of income and their sources- Money income, Real income. Psychic income, Family budget and Savings
\par }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid16343273 
\par Unit \endash IV\tab (20Hours)
\par }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 
\par Management of energy and Ergonomics-Management of energy \endash Planning, Controlling \endash  body mechanics, fatigue- meaning, causes, types, avoidance of fatigue and evaluating.
\par 
\par Work Simplification- meaning, importance, Mundel\lquote s Classes of changes in household activities Ergonomics and work environment -Ergonomics- definition, scope and
 importance. Work place designs in relation to affective, cognitive, temporal, and physical components. Work station design for computer users. Functional designs of Kitchen and other storage areas.
\par 
\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid16343273 U}{\b\insrsid16343273 nit}{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid16343273 - V\tab (20 Hours)
\par }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 
\par Human wants and consumer choice-nature, classification, concept of marginal utility-law of diminishing marginal utility, principles of equi-marginal utility. Consumer market- functions, types of market, price determination in the market. Consumerism- mean
ing of consumer and consumerism, Status of consumer in India-consumer rights and responsibilities, problems faced by consumer and the role of Government and NGO towards consumer protection.
\par 
