FOOD PROCESSING & PACKAG}{\b\insrsid2696901 E}{\b\insrsid15366993 {\*\bkmkstart page22}{\*\bkmkend page22}
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid3866909 {\insrsid15366993 
\par }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid14108498 OBJECTIVES
\par }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 
\par To acquaint with principles of different techniques used in processing and preservation of foods. 
\par To acquaint the students with packaging methods, packaging materials, packaging machineries, modern packaging techniques etc. 
\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid14108498 U}{\b\insrsid2189550 nit}{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid14108498  \endash I\tab (15 Hours)
\par }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15366993 {\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 Scope of food processing, historical developments, principles of food processing and preservation.
\par 
\par Processing and preservation by heat \endash  blanching, pasteurization, sterilization and UHT processing, canning, extrusion cooking, dielectric heating, microwave heating, baking, roasting and frying, etc.
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid3866909 {\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 
\par }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid14108498 U}{\b\insrsid2189550 nit}{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid14108498 - II\tab (10 Hours)
\par }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 
\par Processing and preservation by low \endash  temperature \endash  refrigeration, freezing, CA, MA, and dehydro-freezing.
\par }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid14108498 
\par U}{\b\insrsid2189550 nit }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid14108498 - III\tab (10 Hours)
\par }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 
\par Processing and preservation by drying, concentration and evaporation- types of dryers and their suitability for different food products; ultra \endash  filtration, reverse osmosis.
\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid14108498 U}{\b\insrsid2189550 nit}{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid14108498  \endash IV\tab (20 Hours)
\par }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15366993 {\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 Definitions, objectives and functions of packaging and packa
ging materials; Packaging requirements and selection of packaging materials; Types of packaging materials: Paper: Pulping, fibrillation and beating, types of papers and their testing methods; Glass: composition, properties, types of closures, methods of b
ottle making; Metals: Tinplate containers, tinning process, components of tinplate, tin free steel (TFS), types of cans, aluminum containers,
\par {\*\bkmkstart page23}{\*\bkmkend page23}lacquers; Plastics: types of plastic films, laminated plastic materials, co-extrusion, edible films, biodegradable plastics.
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid3866909 {\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 
\par }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid14108498 U}{\b\insrsid2189550 nit}{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid14108498  \endash V\tab (20 Hours)
\par }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 
\par Food packaging system: Different forms of packaging such as rigid, semi-rigid, flexible forms and different packaging system for (a) dehydrated foods (b) frozen foods (c) dairy products (d) fresh fruits and vegetables (e) meat, poultry and sea foods.

\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid14108498 PRACTICALS\tab (15 Hours)
\par }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 
\par Seaming and testing of cans; Tin coating measurement and tests for sulphide stain and crystal size of tin plates; determination of thermal inactivation time of enzymes; Thermal processing of foo
ds; Dehydration of foods; Refrigeration Freezing of foods; Concentration of foods; Identification and testing of packaging materials; To perform vacuum packaging of food sample and carry out its storage study. Packaging the food material in seal and shrin
k packaging machine and study its shelf life
\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid2189550\charrsid2189550 Reference:}{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid14108498 
\par }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 
