\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid3546002 {\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 To enable the students to}{\insrsid16723390  }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 
Acquire the practical knowledge regarding the working procedure and the production of garments at industrial or commercial level. 
\par To study the current market trends of garments at boutique and industrial level. 
\par To get acquainted with the basic merchandising concepts related to the Fashion Industry. 
\par All the students have to undertake a Internship / Industrial Apprenticeship in any of the
\par Garment Industry / Manufacturing Unit / Designer\rquote s Boutique / Import \endash  Export Unit / Textile Manufacturing Units/ Merchandising Firms etc. for at least 4 weeks before the completion of the
\par {\*\bkmkstart page25}{\*\bkmkend page25}2nd year Degree Course. Results/Mark sheet will be issued only after the submission Internship Report.
\par }{\insrsid3546002 
\par }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 Internship Project After the completion of the II semester, the studen
ts are sent on a one month industry training programme (Project) for gaining substantial hands on experience in the Apparel or Designing industry. There should be an internal assessment and external assessment for the Internship. The internship can be don
e
 individually or as a group of maximum 5 students. However the Viva on these is to be conducted individually. The project report of internship in duplicate should be submitted to the department and are to be produced before the external examiners during t
he oral examination in the II semester.
\par }{\insrsid6777019 
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid3866909 {\insrsid16000594 
