\b\insrsid2745\charrsid8802801  }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid8802801 RESEARCH METHODOLOGY AND STATISTICS
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid3866909 {\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid8802801 
\par }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid16542432 OBJECTIVES
\par }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 
\par To understand the significance of statistics and research methodology in Home Science research 
\par To understand the types, tools and methods of research and develop the ability to construct data gathering instruments appropriate to the research design. 
\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid16542432 U}{\b\insrsid3501514 nit}{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid16542432  \endash  I\tab (15 Hours)
\par }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 
\par Research Methodology- Introduction and meaning of research, objectives of research, types of research and significance of research. Criteria of good research, problems faced by researcher in India.
\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid16542432 U}{\b\insrsid3501514 nit}{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid16542432  \endash  II\tab (20 Hours)
\par }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 
\par Process of Research- Steps involved in research process. Research design: various methods of research design. Sampling design- steps in sample design, various types of sampling design. Measurement scales.
\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid16542432 U}{\b\insrsid3501514 nit}{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid16542432  \endash  III\tab (20 Hours)
\par }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 
\par Methods of Data Collection- Collection of primary data - observation method, interview method, collection of data through questionnaires, guidelines for constructing questionnaire/ schedules. Various methods of data collection. Collection of secondary dat
a, selection of appropriate method of data collection.
\par }{\insrsid6777019 
\par }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid16542432 U}{\b\insrsid3501514 nit}{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid16542432  }{\b\insrsid3501514  - }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid16542432 IV\tab (15 Hours)}{\b\insrsid16542432 {\*\bkmkstart page29}{\*\bkmkend page29} 
\par }{\b\insrsid11692979 
\par }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 Analysis of data- Types of analysis, statistical research, measures of central tendency, dispersion, regression, correlation, association and variance, hypothesis-ty
pes of hypothesis, testing hypothesis- t, z, f test and chi square test.
\par 
\par }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid16542432 U}{\b\insrsid3501514 nit - }{\b\insrsid6777019\charrsid16542432 V\tab (20 Hours)
\par }{\insrsid6777019\charrsid3866909 
\par Interpretation and Report Writing- Meaning of interpretation, technique of interpretation, significance of report writing, steps in writing report, layout of the
 research report. Types of report, precautions for writing research report. Writing proposal publication and funding agencies.
\par 
\par }{\insrsid9928575 
\par 
