\par Counseling Approaches and Techniques \endash  Meaning, Origin, Procedure, Merit and Limitations of counseling approaches; Psychoanalysis approach, Carl Roger\rquote s approach, Rational\endash  Emotive approach; Counseling techniques \endash 
 Client-centered, Counselor-centered and Eclectic counseling.
\par 
\par Types of Counseling - Individual and Group counseling - Tools Required, Types of groups, Process of individual and Group counseling, Merits and Limitations \endash  Situations that lend for group counseling situation
\par 
